# EnergoTS Branch Lock [CRITICAL]

## Rule ENERGOTS.0

**EnergoTS (`Cursor-Project/EnergoTS/`) is locked to the `cursor` branch. No other branch may be checked out.**

### Prohibited

- `git checkout <branch>` / `git switch <branch>` where branch is NOT `cursor`
- `git checkout -b <branch>` (creating new branches)
- Automatic updates from `main` without explicit user request

### Allowed

- `git checkout cursor` / `git switch cursor`
- `git fetch origin main`, `git merge origin/main`, `git pull origin main`, `git rebase origin/main` -- ONLY when user explicitly requests
- All other git operations (commit, push) while on `cursor` branch
- Operations in other directories (Phoenix, etc.) are not restricted

### Enforcement

Hooks `block-energots-branch-switch.ps1` (beforeShellExecution) and `block-energots-branch-requests.ps1` (beforeSubmitPrompt) enforce this rule at the system level.

Before any git branch operation in EnergoTS: verify target branch is `cursor`. If not, BLOCK immediately.

NEVER automatically suggest or perform sync from `main`. Only act when user explicitly says "update cursor from main", "sync with main", "merge main into cursor", etc.

This rule applies ONLY to EnergoTS. Phoenix and other directories are not affected.
